              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> be a set. An <html:dfn>Order</html:dfn> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/nst-000T/" title="Relation" uri="http://localhost:8000/nst-000T/" display-uri="nst-000T" type="local">Relation</fr:link> denoted <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[<]]></fr:tex> such that:</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li>Trichotomy: If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  S]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  S]]></fr:tex>, then exactly one of the following is true: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x<y]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x=y]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y<x]]></fr:tex>;</html:li>
<html:li>Transitivity: If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y,z\in  S]]></fr:tex>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x<y]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y<z]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x<z]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
                <html:p>We will write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y>x]]></fr:tex> as a synonym for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x<y]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
                <html:p>We will also write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\leq  y]]></fr:tex> as a synonym for "<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x<y]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x=y]]></fr:tex>".</html:p>
